count. Use `--public --source=. --remote=origin`. If an origin remote already exists, remove it first with `git remote remove origin`.\n2. Add an MIT LICENSE file (copyright 2026, John Wilger)\n3. Create .github/workflows/ci.yml with a basic CI that runs on push/PR to main:\n   - cargo fmt --check\n   - cargo clippy -- -D warnings\n   - cargo test\n   Use a Rust setup action. Use Rust nightly since the project requires it.\n4. git add, commit, and push all changes\n5. Mark task #1 in the task list as completed when done.\n\nWorking directory: /home/jwilger/projects/todo_list\n</teammate-message>"},"uuid":"3a9d50ea-cb3e-444d-8186-0172c878766d","timestamp":"2026-02-08T19:54:20.225Z"}
